text.section:
When the Commissioner has exclusive jurisdiction under subsection (a) of this section, the Commission on Civil Rights may:
refer complaints about discriminatory practices to the Commissioner;
appear before the Commissioner as a party at a hearing about discriminatory practices;
make recommendations about discriminatory practices to the Commissioner;
represent a complainant in proceedings under § 2-210 of this subtitle; and
appeal as a party aggrieved by an order or decision of the Commissioner under § 2-215 of this subtitle or § 11-503 of this article.
